no.motif.types

Interface HeadAndTail<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - The type of objects which may be retrieved from the head element.
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Elements<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    PreparedIterable

    public interface HeadAndTail<E>
    A recursive type which can be splitted into a head element, and the remaining tail, which may be splitted further into head and tail.

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      Optional<E> head()
      Gets the head, or first element, if it exists.
      HeadAndTail<E> tail()
      Gets the tail, i.e. the remainder after the head.

    • Method Detail

      • head

        Optional<E> head()
        Gets the head, or first element, if it exists.

      • tail

        HeadAndTail<E> tail()
        Gets the tail, i.e. the remainder after the head.
        Returns:
        The tail, which may be empty if there is only a head element.
        Throws:
        NoSuchElementException - if head() is none, so there is no remainder.
